Recursion ka birth kyu hua?

1.Maan lo tumhare paas 100 boxes hain aur har box ke andar kuch aur boxes ho sakte hain.
2.Ab question hai: Total boxes kitne hain?
  Tum kya karoge?
   1.Ek box kholo.
   2.Agar usme aur boxes hain to unhe bhi count karo.
   3.Har inner box ke liye wahi kaam repeat karo. (step1 + step2 )

Note:-problem ka solution exactly problem jaisa hi lag raha hai
"Ek box count karo + andar ke boxes ka count"
Yahi recursion hai.

Mathematics se aayi recursion
1.Computers se pehle mathematicians recursive definitions use karte the.
    Factorial:-
         !5 = 5 * !4
         !4 = 4 * !3
         !3 = 3 * !2
         !2 = 2 * !1
         !1 = 1
Yaha ek badi problem ko chhoti same-type problem me convert kar diya.
Isi idea ko programmers ne functions me implement kar diya.

int fact(n){
    if(n==1)  return 1;

    return n * fact(n-1);
}

Computer Science me recursion ka birth
1.Jab early programming languages develop hui (especially Lisp),researchers ne dekha ki:
  Bahut saari cheezein naturally recursive hoti hain:
  a.Tree traversal
  b.Directory structure
  c.Mathematical formulas
  d.Divide and Conquer algorithms

Isliye languages ne function ko khud ko call karne ki capability di.


step1: Loop ki soch vs Recursion ki soch
a.Loop sochta hai
i = 0
jab tak i < n:
  kaam karo
  i++
State bahar maintain hoti hai. Tum khud track karte ho. 

b.Recursion sochta hai
f(n):
  agar base case → return
  kaam karo
  f(n-1) ya f(chhota)
State function ke andar hai. Stack khud track karta hai.

step2:Recursion ki hidden requirement
3 cheezein honi chahiye — inke bina recursion nahi likhoge
1. Base case
Kab rukna hai?
n==0, i==len, node==null

2. Recursive call
Problem chhoti kaise hogi?
n-1, i+1, node.left

3. Answer build
Wapas aate kaise jodte hain?
return + kuch, max(left,right)

step3:Recursion ki soch kab toot jaati hai?
Example: Max Subarray — [-2, 1, -3, 4, -1, 2, 1, -5, 4]
f(n) = max subarray in first n elements

kya f(n) = kuch + f(n-1)? → NAHI
kyunki subarray contiguous hona chahiye
aur n-1 ka answer n ke liye useful nahi
Jab "mujhe poori history chahiye future decision ke liye" — recursion akele fail hoga. Wahan Kadane ya DP chahiye.

step4:Har recursion question se pehle ye 5 sawaal poochho

Q1
Main optimize kya kar raha hun?
sum? count? yes/no? min/max?

Q2
Base case kya hai?
Kab rukna hai? Kaunsi input pe trivially answer pata hai?

Q3
Problem chhoti kaise hogi?
n-1? i+1? left child? smaller string?

Q4
Har call pe kya choice hai?
Include/exclude? Left/right? Continue/start new?

Q5
Answer kaise build hoga?
Return value? Global variable? Parameter mein pass?


Step 5 — 8-step process har question ke liye
Ye teri existing framework — recursion ke liye adapt ki gayi
01
Question apni language mein todho
Jo poochha hai usse apne words mein likhо — "mujhe X chahiye, input Y hai, constraint Z hai"
02
Input observe karo
Array hai? String? Tree? Graph? N kya hai? Edge cases kya hain?
03
Brute force socho — recursion se hi
Sabse seedha recursive solution likhо — TLE aaye toh bhi theek
04
Repeated subproblems identify karo
Kya same f(n) baar baar call ho raha hai? Recursion tree banao
05
Pattern identify karo
Ye kis type ka recursion hai? — Linear / Tree / Backtrack / Divide&Conquer
06
Generic template banao
Base case likhо, recursive call likhо, answer build karo — pseudocode mein
07
Dry run karo — stack trace karo
Chhote input pe manually har call trace karo — paper pe
08
Code likhо
Template se code mein convert karo — edge cases check karo



